data.name: HVAC Product Type Library Example
data.description: Demonstrates an air terminal type, which may be instantiated in buildings within referencing files.

data.name: Acme Diffuser 1234
data.description: Ceiling diffuser

data.name: PortNumber
data.description: The port index for logically ordering the port within the containing element or element type.

data.name: ColorCode
data.description: Name of a color for identifying the connector, if applicable.

data.name: Pset_DistributionPortCommon
data.description: Common attributes attached to an instance of IfcDistributionPort.

data.name: Pset_DistributionPortCommon
data.description: Common attributes attached to an instance of IfcDistributionPort.

data.name: ConnectionType
data.description:
The end-style treatment of the duct port:

BEADEDSLEEVE: Beaded Sleeve. 
COMPRESSION: Compression. 
CRIMP: Crimp. 
DRAWBAND: Drawband. 
DRIVESLIP: Drive slip. 
FLANGED: Flanged. 
OUTSIDESLEEVE: Outside Sleeve. 
SLIPON: Slipon. 
SOLDERED: Soldered. 
SSLIP: S-Slip. 
STANDINGSEAM: Standing seam. 
SWEDGE: Swedge. 
WELDED: Welded. 
OTHER: Another type of end-style has been applied.
NONE: No end-style has been applied.

data.name: ConnectionSubType
data.description: The physical port connection subtype that further qualifies the ConnectionType.

data.name: NominalWidth
data.description: The nominal width or diameter of the duct connection.

data.name: NominalHeight
data.description: The nominal height of the duct connection.

data.name: DryBulbTemperature
data.description: Dry bulb temperature of the air.

data.name: WetBulbTemperature
data.description: Wet bulb temperature of the air.

data.name: VolumetricFlowRate
data.description: The volumetric flow rate of the fluid.

data.name: Velocity
data.description: The velocity of the fluid.

data.name: Pressure
data.description: The pressure of the fluid.

data.name: Pset_DistributionPortTypeAirConditioning
data.description: Duct port occurrence attributes attached to an instance of IfcDistributionPort.

data.name: Reference
data.description: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), provided, if there is no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.

data.name: Status
data.description: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

data.name: Shape
data.description: Shape of the air terminal. Slot is typically a long narrow supply device with an aspect ratio generally greater than 10 to 1.

data.name: FaceType
data.description: Identifies how the terminal face of an AirTerminal is constructed.

data.name: SlotWidth
data.description: Slot width.

data.name: SlotLength
data.description: Slot length.

data.name: NumberOfSlots
data.description: Number of slots.

data.name: FlowPattern
data.description: Flow pattern.

data.name: AirFlowrateRange
data.description: Air flowrate range within which the air terminal is designed to operate.

data.name: TemperatureRange
data.description: Temperature range within which the air terminal is designed to operate.

data.name: DischargeDirection
data.description:
Discharge direction of the air terminal.

Parallel: discharges parallel to mounting surface designed so that flow attaches to the surface.
Perpendicular:  discharges away from mounting surface.
Adjustable: both parallel and perpendicular discharge.

data.name: ThrowLength
data.description: The horizontal or vertical axial distance an airstream travels after leaving an AirTerminal before the maximum stream velocity is reduced to a specified terminal velocity under isothermal conditions at the upper value of the AirFlowrateRange.

data.name: AirDiffusionPerformanceIndex
data.description: The Air Diffusion Performance Index (ADPI) is used for cooling mode conditions. If several measurements of air velocity and air temperature are made throughout the occupied zone of a space, the ADPI is the percentage of locations where measurements were taken that meet the specifications for effective draft temperature and air velocity.

data.name: FinishType
data.description: The type of finish for the air terminal.

data.name: FinishColor
data.description: The finish color for the air terminal.

data.name: MountingType
data.description:
The way the air terminal is mounted to the ceiling, wall, etc.

Surface: mounted to the surface of something (e.g., wall, duct, etc.).
Flat flush: mounted flat and flush with a surface.
Lay-in: mounted in a lay-in type ceiling (e.g., a dropped ceiling grid).

data.name: CoreType
data.description: Identifies the way the core of the AirTerminal is constructed.

data.name: CoreSetHorizontal
data.description: Degree of horizontal (in the X-axis of the LocalPlacement) blade set from the centerline.

data.name: CoreSetVertical
data.description: Degree of vertical (in the Y-axis of the LocalPlacement) blade set from the centerline.

data.name: HasIntegralControl
data.description: If TRUE, a self powered temperature control is included in the AirTerminal.

data.name: FlowControlType
data.description: Type of flow control element that may be included as a part of the construction of the air terminal.

data.name: HasSoundAttenuator
data.description: If TRUE, the air terminal has sound attenuation.

data.name: HasThermalInsulation
data.description: If TRUE, the air terminal has thermal insulation.

data.name: NeckArea
data.description: Neck area of the air terminal.

data.name: EffectiveArea
data.description: Effective discharge area of the air terminal.

data.name: AirFlowrateVersusFlowControlElement
data.description: Air flowrate versus flow control element position at nominal pressure drop.

data.name: Pset_AirTerminalTypeCommon
data.description:
Air terminal type common attributes.
SoundLevel attribute deleted in IFC2x2 Pset Addendum: Use IfcSoundProperties instead.

data.name: GlobalTradeItemNumber
data.description: The Global Trade Item Number (GTIN) is an identifier for trade items developed by GS1 (www.gs1.org).

data.name: ArticleNumber
data.description: Article number or reference that is be applied to a configured product according to a standard scheme for article number definition as defined by the manufacturer. It is often used as the purchasing number.

data.name: ModelReference
data.description: The model number or designator of the product model (or product line) as assigned by the manufacturer of the manufactured item.

data.name: ModelLabel
data.description: The descriptive model name of the product model (or product line) as assigned by the manufacturer of the manufactured item.

data.name: Manufacturer
data.description: The organization that manufactured and/or assembled the item.

data.name: ProductionYear
data.description: The year of production of the manufactured item.

data.name: AssemblyPlace
data.description: Enumeration defining where the assembly is intended to take place, either in a factory or on the building site.

data.name: Pset_ManufacturerTypeInformation
data.description:
Defines characteristics of types (ranges) of manufactured products that may be given by the manufacturer. Note that the term 'manufactured' may also be used to refer to products that are supplied and identified by the supplier or that are assembled off site by a third party provider. 
HISTORY: This property set replaces the entity IfcManufacturerInformation from previous IFC releases. IFC 2x4: AssemblyPlace property added.
